    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Ah I think what I missed in the custom widget, you need to call helper.search() at the end of the line:\n\n``` js\n options.helper.setQueryParameter('restrictSearchableAttributes', ...);\n options.helper.search();\n```\n\nI just tried this and it worked well:\n\n``` js\nvar algoliasearch = require(\"algoliasearch\");\nvar helper = require(\"algoliasearch-helper\")\nvar client = algoliasearch('appid', 'key');\nvar helper = helper(client, 'indexName');\nhelper.setQueryParameter('restrictSearchableAttributes', ['categories']);\nhelper.search()\nhelper.setQueryParameter('restrictSearchableAttributes'); // not sent\nhelper.search()\n```\n\nThe \"helper\" you are using is this: https://github.com/algolia/algoliasearch-helper-js\n",
